metadata.name: Pride
metadata.description:
But the proud man that is clothed
With momentary, momentary greatness.
And so sure of himself that he does not remember,
That he is as fragile as glass, He is before the sky.
He is as a wicked monkey, 
And so that the angels weep over him,
Which, had they been mortal, would have wept, 
Would probably have laughed themselves to death.
